BARBERTON – According to organisers, no late registrations will be accepted. The BPN will be held over seven days between June 16 to 22 June with no rest days. Read More: Saturday will be a practice day and normal fees and indemnities apply. Barberton is South Africa’s premier winter flying site. Also, several South Africa paragliding nationals have been held in Barberton. The entry fee is R3 500 and competing per day is R550.